  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "para_id": "Q001117.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(i 1) For Lugal-emuš ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001117.2",
      "line_range": "2",
      "translation": "(i 2) En-metena , ruler of Lagaš , chosen by Nanše in the heart , chief governor of Ninĝirsu , child of En-ana-tum , ruler of Lagaš , built the sanctuary of Dugru for Ninĝirsu , built him the A-huš , the temple that is looked upon with favour , and made them worthy of him . He fashioned him the chariot that heaps up the foreign lands for Ninĝirsu , the \" May all bow down !\" of the road to Eridug , whose fearsomeness ( reaches ) until the heart of the foreign lands . He built him the E-dur-zile ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001117.23",
      "line_range": "23",
      "translation": "(iii 3) For Lugal-Uruba he built his great temple in Urub . For Nanše he built the E-engur in Zulum , and made it worthy of her ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001117.30",
      "line_range": "30",
      "translation": "(iii 10) He released ( the people of ) Lagaš , let the mother return to ( her ) child , and let the child return to ( its ) mother . He remitted the barley-loan debts ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001117.36",
      "line_range": "36",
      "translation": "(iv 6) At that time for Lugal-emuš En-metena built and restored the E-muš in Patibira , his beloved temple . He released the citizens of Unug , Larsam and Patibira . He returned them to Unug under Inana’s authority , returned them to Larsam under Utu’s authority ; and returned to the to E-muš under Lugal-emuš’s authority ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001117.56",
      "line_range": "56",
      "translation": "(vi 7) The personal god of En-metena , who submits to the orders of Inana , is Šul-MUŠxPA ."
    }
  ],
